			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: gear questions <a name="45039"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 8 04 6:49 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=711194
<br />

<br />

<br />
most of the items on that magelo were under 2k and all but a couple (cloak of pernicity and architect's bp) were under 5k.  I used an Iron Breastplate of the Demented before the Architects bp and a Crinoise Cape of the Werewolf before the Pernicity cloak.
<br />

<br />
I play on FV, so very few things are no-drop.  A few of my items are no-drop on normal servers (a couple of my weapons particularly) and wouldn't really be feasible for you, but most are droppable.
<br />

<br />
Note that many of them have recommended levels so if you get them early you won't get full stats.  I kind of like that as it gives a bonus for leveling as you grow into your gear, but at low enough levels it's just not worth wearing the stuff.  
<br />

<br />
I assembled that kit by shopping in the bazaar over several months (&amp; a few items were hand me downs from my guild, &lt;3 Molto)  For each slot I would filter by bard and HP, then bard and STA, then bard and CHA, to see what was available in my price range. (You might choose other stats to focus on; those are mine, in approximately that order.) I didn't rush any purchases, but got to know what items were tasty and what the typical price range was. Then if I saw something at a good price I could snap it up.  By doing that I got a number of what I consider to be good deals, including quite a few things I've been able to resell easily at a profit after I upgraded. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=711194><b>Mellia</b></a>, 53 Bard<br>Molto Espressivo, FV<br><i>Lil sis of 
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94293><b>Valya Wanderfoot</b></a><br>
65 Paladin,  Dark Bane, MM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
